  "prompt": "Can I get infected with an STD from getting oral sex without protection?",
  "response": "Yes, you can contract sexually transmitted diseases (STDs) through oral sex without protection. Some STDs that can be transmitted include:\n\n1. Herpes\n2. HPV (Human Papillomavirus)\n3. Chlamydia\n4. Gonorrhea\n5. Syphilis\n6. HIV (though less common)\n\nUsing dental dams or condoms can help reduce transmission risk. Getting tested regularly and communicating with sexual partners about sexual health is important.",
